iter59 (2026-05-26, 0.1.592): tree-stability bound WITNESSED working end-to-end. query_at_bounded (rs-learn 9e8e525, shipped 0.1.592): memorized 4 facts in a test ns (4 auto-edges under hub), query_at unbounded=4, query_at{limit:2}=2 most-recent edges (recency-ordered, newest first, history preserved). DESIGN: limit is the AGENT-FACING knob (consumer = whoever queries on demand), NOT a forced internal default - a default would silently drop edges a consumer wanted; store-everything-retrieve-bounded is the correct general-graph surface. Deviations this window (3) all from the iter58 plan-slip (2x prd-resolve-unknown-id from resolving-before-adding) + a heavy-work long-gap; the plan-slip cost validated the lesson, applied this turn (full PRD before executing). LESSON: bounded retrieval over an auto-growing graph = the right tree-stability shape; cap at query-time by recency, never delete history.